'''政客'''（{{Lang-en|Politico}}）是[[美国|美国]]一家总部位于[[弗吉尼亚州|弗吉尼亚州]][[阿靈頓縣_(維吉尼亞州)|阿灵顿县]]的{{Link-en|政治新闻|Political journalism}}公司，其报道范围涵盖了美国乃至全球的政治及政策内容。政客通过其旗下的报纸、杂志、电视、网站及播客分发其内容。其针对[[华盛顿特区|华盛顿特区]]的报道包括对美国的[[美国国会|国会]]、[[美国游说|游说]]、[[美国媒体|媒体]]和[[美国总统|总统]]的关注<ref>{{cite web |title=Mission Statement |url=https://www.politico.com/aboutus/missionstatement.html |publisher=Politico |accessdate=2020-11-23 |archive-date=2016-03-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304053309/http://www.politico.com/aboutus/missionstatement.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2021年8月，德国的欧洲最大新闻出版商[[阿克塞爾·斯普林格集團|阿克塞爾·斯普林格集團]]宣布以10亿美元高价向网站创办人罗伯特·奥尔布里顿收购公司。交易于同年10月底达成<ref name=polacq>{{Cite web |url=https://www.axelspringer.com/en/press-releases/axel-springer-completes-acquisition-of-politico |title=Axel Springer Completes Acquisition of POLITICO |date=2021-10-19 |access-date=2022-05-07 |publisher=Axel Springer |archive-date=2021-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211026221805/https://www.axelspringer.com/en/press-releases/axel-springer-completes-acquisition-of-politico }}</ref>。在新东家的带领下，员工规模大幅度增加，部分新闻内容设置了[[付费墙|付费墙]]<ref name=as>{{Cite web |url=https://www.cnbc.com/2021/08/26/axel-springer-to-buy-politico.html |title=Politico sells to German publishing giant Axel Springer in deal worth about $1 billion |first1=Lauren |last1=Feiner |first2=Alex |last2=Sherman |date=2021-08-26 |website=CNBC |access-date=2022-05-07 |archive-date=2022-04-15 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220415201500/https://www.cnbc.com/2021/08/26/axel-springer-to-buy-politico.html }}</ref><ref name="wsj">{{cite news |last1=Pancevski |first1=Bojan |title=Politico's New Owner Plans to Grow Staff, Launch Paywall |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/politicos-new-owner-plans-to-grow-staff-launch-paywall-11634325249 |access-date=2021-10-16 |publisher=Wall Street Journal |date=2021-10-15 |archive-date=2021-10-15 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20211015213358/https://www.wsj.com/articles/politicos-new-owner-plans-to-grow-staff-launch-paywall-11634325249 }}</ref>。

== 发展历史 ==
=== 起源、风格与发展 ===
2007年1月23日，在{{tsl|en|Robert Allbritton|罗伯特·奥尔布里顿}}的资助下，由《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》前记者{{tsl|en|John F. Harris|约翰·F·哈里斯}}和{{tsl|en|Jim VandeHei|吉姆·范德黑}}创办的政客网站正式上线<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |last=Uberti |first=David |date=2015-06-25 |title=Can Politico rise again? |language=en |work=Columbia Journalism Review |url=https://www.cjr.org/the_profile/can_politico_rise_again.php |access-date=2017-07-28 |archive-date=2020-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522205139/https://www.cjr.org/the_profile/can_politico_rise_again.php }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=McPherson |first=Lindsey |year=2008 |title=Politico Animal |url=http://ajrarchive.org/article.asp?id=4587 |access-date=2017-07-28 |website=American Journalism Review}}</ref>，以快节奏的互联报道提供极其细节化的政治新闻，风格类似于{{tsl|en|SportsCenter|体育中心}}<ref>{{Cite news |last=Smith |first=Ben |date=2021-01-03 |title=They Seem to Think the Next Four Years Will Be Normal |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/03/business/media/punchbowl-playbook-capitol-hill-politics.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20211228/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/03/business/media/punchbowl-playbook-capitol-hill-politics.html |archive-date=2021-12-28 |url-access=limited |issn=0362-4331 }}{{cbignore}}</ref>或[[ESPN|ESPN]]<ref>{{Cite news |last=Leibovich |first=Mark |date=2010-04-21 |title=The Man the White House Wakes Up To |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/04/25/magazine/25allen-t.html |issn=0362-4331 |accessdate=2022-05-07 |archive-date=2013-02-16 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130216141734/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/04/25/magazine/25allen-t.html?_r=0 }}</ref>的赛事分析。首批员工包括《[[时代杂志|时代杂志]]》专栏作家{{tsl|en|Michael Allen (journalist)|迈克·艾伦}}<ref name=":4">{{Cite news |last=Leibovich |first=Mark |date=2010-04-25 |title=Politico's Mike Allen, the Man the White House Wakes Up To |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/04/25/magazine/25allen-t.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2013-02-16 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130216141734/http://www.nytimes.com/2010/04/25/magazine/25allen-t.html?_r=0 }}</ref>及担任网站首任总裁兼首席执行官的{{tsl|en|Fred Ryan|弗雷德·莱恩}}<ref>{{Cite web |last=Allen |first=Mike |date=2007-05-04 |title=Politico Playbook: Mitt's moment |url=https://www.politico.com/news/stories/0507/3841.html |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160406160005/http://www.politico.com/story/2007/05/politico-playbook-mitts-moment-003841 |archive-date=2016-04-06 |access-date=2016-05-10 |publisher=Politico}}</ref>。另外创始团队还包括{{tsl|en|Martin Tolchin|马丁·托尔钦}}<ref>{{Cite news |last=Diamond |first=Dan |date=2020-02-24 |title=Trump set to ask for more coronavirus cash |work=Politico |url=https://www.politico.com/newsletters/politico-pulse/2020/02/24/trump-set-to-ask-for-more-coronavirus-cash-785616 |access-date=2020-05-07 |quote=Martin Tolchin, the founder of The Hill and a member of POLITICO's founding editorial team |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015536/https://www.politico.com/newsletters/politico-pulse/2020/02/24/trump-set-to-ask-for-more-coronavirus-cash-785616 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Martin Tolchin |work=Politico |url=https://www.politico.com/staff/martin-tolchin |access-date=2020-05-07 |quote=he is helping launch Politico |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015621/https://www.politico.com/staff/martin-tolchin }}</ref>。

从创始之日开始，网站就会带着摄像机跑遍大大小小的政治活动<ref name="washingtonian">{{Cite web |last=Jaffe |first=Harry |date=2007-01-22 |title=Politico Hopes To Rock Washington Media |url=http://www.washingtonian.com/articles/mediapolitics/3148.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120205063344/http://www.washingtonian.com/articles/mediapolitics/3148.html |archive-date=2012-02-05 |website=Washingtonian}}</ref>，在别的地方宣扬自己的工作<ref name="InternationalHeraldTribune">{{Cite news |last=Seelye |first=Katharine Q. |date=2007-01-08 |title=For journalists, it's not politics as usual |work=International Herald Tribune |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2007/01/08/technology/08iht-washington.4136182.html |accessdate=2022-05-07 |archive-date=2012-01-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119131128/https://www.nytimes.com/2007/01/08/technology/08iht-washington.4136182.html }}</ref>。到2008年，网站月访问量突破300万次<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pérez-Peña |first=Richard |date=2008-12-14 |title=Politico and Reuters Forge News-Distribution Alliance |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/12/15/business/media/15politico.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2018-01-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105204725/http://www.nytimes.com/2008/12/15/business/media/15politico.html }}</ref>。

2008年9月，《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》报道网站会在[[2008年美国总统选举|2008年美国总统选举]]后扩展业务范围，新聘用记者、编辑、网页工程师等岗位的员工，扩大报纸在华盛顿地区的发行量，提升报纸的发行频率<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pérez-Peña, Richard |date=2008-09-22 |title=Politico Intends to Expand After Presidential Race Ends |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/22/business/media/22politico.html |accessdate=2022-05-07 |archive-date=2012-03-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120325032209/https://www.nytimes.com/2008/09/22/business/media/22politico.html }}</ref>。2008年到[[2012年美国选举|2012]]大选期间，员工规模增加突增三倍<ref>{{Cite news |last=Peters |first=Jeremy W. |date=2011-01-29 |title=Political News Sites See 2012 as Breakthrough Year |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/30/business/media/30blogs.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2012-01-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120105083320/https://www.nytimes.com/2011/01/30/business/media/30blogs.html }}</ref>，其中包括以评论员身份加盟的政治评论员[[迈克·金斯利|迈克·金斯利]]和[[喬·斯卡伯勒|喬·斯卡伯勒]]<ref>{{Cite news |last=Smith |first=Ben |date=2010-09-08 |title=Kinsley, Scarborough to Politico |work=Politico |url=https://www.politico.com/blogs/bensmith/0910/Kinsley_Scarborough_to_POLITICO_.html |access-date=2017-07-27 |archive-date=2013-05-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130514093223/http://www.politico.com/blogs/bensmith/0910/Kinsley_Scarborough_to_POLITICO_.html }}</ref>。2009年，网页版名称正式从“The Politico”缩短为“Politico”。

2011年，网站开始着重于{{tsl|en|long-form journalism|长篇新闻}}和新闻分析<ref name=":0" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Filloux |first=Frédéric |date=2011-09-05 |title=Politico: what are the secrets of its success? |language=en-GB |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2011/sep/05/politico-secrets-success |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015540/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2011/sep/05/politico-secrets-success }}</ref>。这种报道内容上的转变随着2013年6月{{tsl|en|Susan Glasser|苏珊·格拉泽}}获聘、负责监督“外界人士的重要观点”及“长篇报道”而得到进一步支持<ref name=":6">{{Cite news |last=Kaufman |first=Leslie |date=2013-06-03 |title=Politico Expands Coverage Areas and Adds an Editor of Note |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/06/03/business/media/politico-expands-coverage-areas-and-adds-an-editor-of-note.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2020-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522210142/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/06/03/business/media/politico-expands-coverage-areas-and-adds-an-editor-of-note.html }}</ref>。2014年9月，格拉泽被任命为网站新任编辑，接替上月辞职的理查德·波尔克（Richard Berke）<ref>{{Cite news |last=Somaiya |first=Ravi |date=2014-09-18 |title=Politico Names New Overseer of Washington News Content |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/19/business/media/susan-glasser-named-top-editor-at-politico.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2014-09-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140921020542/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/09/19/business/media/susan-glasser-named-top-editor-at-politico.html }}</ref>。

2013年10月，范黑德获任命为网站新任首席执行官<ref>{{Cite news |last1=Stelter |first1=Brian |last2=Kaufman |first2=Leslie |date=2013-10-13 |title=VandeHei, Politico Editor, Is Made Chief Executive |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2013/10/14/business/media/politico-editor-given-chief-executive-title.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2013-10-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017021024/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/10/14/business/media/politico-editor-given-chief-executive-title.html }}</ref>。在他的带领下，网站继续蓬勃发展，仅2014年一年的营收就增长了25%<ref>{{Cite web |last=Ingram |first=Mathew |date=2015-09-28 |title=Can Politico save political journalism, not just in the U.S. but in Europe too? |url=http://fortune.com/2015/09/28/politico-save-journalism/ |access-date=2017-07-28 |website=Fortune |archive-date=2018-09-24 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180924033337/http://fortune.com/2015/09/28/politico-save-journalism/ }}</ref>。到2016年，网站在全球各地有将近500名员工<ref>{{Cite news |last=Somaiya |first=Ravi |date=2016-01-29 |title=Leaders Deny Strife Caused Departures From Politico |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/30/business/media/leaders-deny-strife-caused-departures-from-politico.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2016-02-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160202190451/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/30/business/media/leaders-deny-strife-caused-departures-from-politico.html }}</ref>。

伴随着外界报道团队内部关系紧张，范黑德和艾伦宣布在[[2016年美国总统选举|2016年美国总统选举]]后离巢<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":7">{{Cite news |last=Somaiya |first=Ravi |date=2016-01-28 |title=Politico Will Lose Its Co-Founder and 4 Others |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/29/business/media/politico-mike-allen-jim-vandehei-leaving.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2017-07-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170728075456/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/01/29/business/media/politico-mike-allen-jim-vandehei-leaving.html }}</ref>，由奥尔布里顿接任范黑德的首席执行官职务<ref name=":7" />。2017年到2021年，投资银行家帕特里克·斯蒂尔（Patrick Steel）出任首席执行官<ref>{{Cite news |last=Alpert |first=Lukas I. |date=2017-04-25 |title=Politico Names Investment Banker as New CEO |language=en-US |work=Wall Street Journal |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/politico-names-investment-banker-as-new-ceo-1493114400 |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0099-9660 |archive-date=2017-10-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171019001127/https://www.wsj.com/articles/politico-names-investment-banker-as-new-ceo-1493114400 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Robertson |first=Katie |date=2021-02-02 |title=Politico's chief executive is stepping down this year. |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/02/business/Patrick-Steel-politico.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20211228/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/02/02/business/Patrick-Steel-politico.html |archive-date=2021-12-28 |url-access=limited }}{{cbignore}}</ref>。曾任公共广播电台{{tsl|en|WNYC-FM|WNYC-FM}}首席执行官的戈利·谢赫霍尔斯拉米（Goli Sheikholeslami）于2022年1月获任命为新任首席执行官<ref>{{Cite news |last=Robertson |first=Katie |date=2022-01-10 |title=The head of New York Public Radio will take charge of Politico. |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2022/01/10/business/politico-goli-sheikholeslami-new-york-public-radio.html |access-date=2022-04-11 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2022-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220411190348/https://www.nytimes.com/2022/01/10/business/politico-goli-sheikholeslami-new-york-public-radio.html }}</ref>。2022年3月，曾任[[MSNBC|MSNBC]]和[[NBC新闻|NBC新闻]]记者的{{le|达芙娜·林泽|Dafna Linzer}}获任命为新任首席执行官<ref>{{Cite web |last=Johnson |first=Ted |date=2022-03-23 |title=Dafna Linzer Named Executive Editor Of Politico |url=https://deadline.com/2022/03/dafna-linzer-politico-executive-editor-1234985241/ |access-date=2022-04-11 |website=Deadline |language=en-US |archive-date=2022-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220411183146/https://deadline.com/2022/03/dafna-linzer-politico-executive-editor-1234985241/ }}</ref>。

=== Politico Playbook ===
2007年6月25日<ref>{{Cite web |last=Allen |first=Mike |date=2007-06-25 |title=Politico Playbook: Hijacked |url=https://www.politico.com/playbook/0607/7.html |access-date=2017-07-27 |website=Politico |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015600/https://www.politico.com/playbook/0607/7.html }}</ref>，迈克·米伦推出日更的晨间电邮通讯Playbook（直译为剧本）<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Allen |first1=Mike |last2=Lippman |first2=Daniel |date=2016-07-10 |title=Mike Allen's last Playbook: #3,304, a streak that started June 25, 2007 – Who'll Be First? Obama shops for a country club, and The Atlantic shops for an editor – B'Day: Julianna Smoot, Sam Stein |url=https://www.politico.com/tipsheets/playbook/2016/07/mike-allens-last-playbook-3-304-a-streak-that-started-june-25-2007-wholl-be-first-obama-shops-for-a-country-club-and-the-atlantic-shops-for-an-editor-bday-julianna-smoot-sam-stein-215237 |access-date=2017-07-28 |website=Politico |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015538/https://www.politico.com/tipsheets/playbook/2016/07/mike-allens-last-playbook-3-304-a-streak-that-started-june-25-2007-wholl-be-first-obama-shops-for-a-country-club-and-the-atlantic-shops-for-an-editor-bday-julianna-smoot-sam-stein-215237 }}</ref><ref name=":1">{{Cite web |last=Mullins |first=Luke |date=2016-07-17 |title=The Inside Story of the Politico Break-Up |url=https://www.washingtonian.com/2016/07/17/politico-breakup-vandehei-allbritton-allen/ |access-date=2017-07-28 |website=Washingtonian |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015537/https://www.washingtonian.com/2016/07/17/politico-breakup-vandehei-allbritton-allen/ }}</ref>。仅仅几年，Playbook就在华盛顿地区收割大批读者<ref name=":4" />。到2016年，超过10万名“内部人士、外部人士、说客、记者、州长、参议员、现任总统、未来的总统”每天都会读Playbook<ref name=":5">{{Cite news |last=Rutenberg |first=Jim |date=2016-06-19 |title=Mike Allen, Politico's Newsletter Pioneer, Is Handing Over the Reins |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/20/business/media/mike-allen-politicos-newsletter-pioneer-is-handing-over-the-reins.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108125728/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/20/business/media/mike-allen-politicos-newsletter-pioneer-is-handing-over-the-reins.html }}</ref>。外界认为艾伦和Playbook深刻影响全国政治新闻的语调及意义<ref name=":4" /><ref name=":5" /><ref>{{Cite news |last=Somaiya |first=Ravi |date=2014-01-15 |title=Washington Post and Politico Talk About a Rift |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2014/01/16/business/media/washington-post-and-politico-talk-about-a-rift.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327020218/https://www.nytimes.com/2014/01/16/business/media/washington-post-and-politico-talk-about-a-rift.html }}</ref>。

2014年6月，丹尼尔·李普曼（Daniel Lippman）加盟网站，协助艾伦完成Playbook的工作<ref>{{Cite news |last=Massella |first=Nick |date=2014-06-02 |title=''Politico'' Hires 'Citizen Journo' Daniel Lippman for Playbook |language=en-US |work=AdWeek |url=http://www.adweek.com/digital/politico-hires-citizen-journo-daniel-lippman-for-playbook/ |access-date=2017-07-28 |archive-date=2020-10-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021194922/https://www.adweek.com/digital/politico-hires-citizen-journo-daniel-lippman-for-playbook/ }}</ref>。2016年7月艾伦离职后，安娜·帕梅尔和{{tsl|en|Jake Sherman (journalist)|杰克·谢尔曼}}加盟，接任Playbook的编采工作<ref>{{Cite web |last=Beaujon |first=Andrew |date=2016-07-08 |title=Mike Allen's Last Playbook Is on Sunday |url=https://www.washingtonian.com/2016/07/08/mike-allens-last-playbook-is-on-sunday/ |access-date=2017-07-28 |website=Washingtonian |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015540/https://www.washingtonian.com/2016/07/08/mike-allens-last-playbook-is-on-sunday/ }}</ref>。2017年3月，网站宣布推出Playbook的午间版《Playbook Power Briefing》，采用晨间版的班底<ref>{{Cite news |last=Mullin |first=Benjamin |date=2017-03-20 |title=For a speedier D.C. news cycle, Politico is rolling out a second Playbook |language=en-US |work=Poynter Institute |url=http://www.poynter.org/2017/for-a-speedier-d-c-news-cycle-politico-is-rolling-out-a-second-playbook/452898/ |access-date=2017-07-28 |archive-date=2017-08-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812055533/http://www.poynter.org/2017/for-a-speedier-d-c-news-cycle-politico-is-rolling-out-a-second-playbook/452898/ }}</ref>。2017年，Playbook每周广告费在5万到6万美元之间<ref name=":2">{{Cite news |last=Wemple |first=Erik |date=2016-01-28 |title=Politico implodes |language=en-US |newspaper=The Washington Post |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/erik-wemple/wp/2016/01/28/politico-implodes/ |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0190-8286 |archive-date=2021-01-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210113144534/https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/erik-wemple/wp/2016/01/28/politico-implodes/ }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Watson |first=Libby |date=2018-05-11 |title=Politico Playbook Can Fuck Right Off |url=https://splinternews.com/politico-playbook-can-fuck-right-off-1825951911 |website=Splinter News |access-date=2022-05-07 |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015537/https://splinternews.com/politico-playbook-can-fuck-right-off-1825951911 }}</ref>。帕梅尔和谢尔曼跳槽到{{tsl|en|Punchbowl News|大酒杯新闻}}后，网站于2021年宣布Playbook采用全新班底，成员包括{{tsl|en|Rachael Bade|瑞秋·巴德}}、{{tsl|en|Ryan Lizza|瑞恩·丽莎}}、{{tsl|en|Tara Palmeri|塔拉·帕尔梅里}}和尤金·丹尼尔斯（Eugene Daniels）<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-01-15 |title=Politico Announces Its New Playbook Team {{!}} Washingtonian (DC) |url=https://www.washingtonian.com/2021/01/15/politico-announces-its-new-playbook-team/ |access-date=2022-04-11 |website=Washingtonian |language=en-US |archive-date=2022-04-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220412160507/https://www.washingtonian.com/2021/01/15/politico-announces-its-new-playbook-team/ }}</ref>。

=== 专业版 ===
专业版于2010年上线<ref name=":3">{{Cite news |last=Peters |first=Jeremy W. |date=2010-10-25 |title=Politico Adds Subscription News Service |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/26/business/media/26politico.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2022-04-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220418232549/https://www.nytimes.com/2010/10/26/business/media/26politico.html }}</ref>，提供约100名记者撰写的深入报道，内容涵盖十多个重要议题<ref name=":3" /><ref>{{Cite web |title=Politico Pro |url=https://www.politico.com/pro |access-date=2017-07-28 |website=Politico |language=en |archive-date=2022-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220506050156/https://www.politico.com/pro }}</ref>。专业版按议题收费，若只订阅一个议题，一年的收费会超过1000万美元<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":3" />。尽管有付费前，专业版的续订率还是高达93%，订阅收入占网站总收入四分之一<ref name=":0" /><ref name=":1" />。与此同时，主站及Playbook的内容保持免费<ref name=":3" />。

===杂志版===
2013年11月，双月刊《政客杂志》（''Politico Magazine''）在线上及线下出版<ref name="Hare">{{cite web |last=Kristen |first=Hare |url=https://www.poynter.org/reporting-editing/2013/politico-magazine-launches-online/ |title=Politico magazine launches online |website=Poynter Institute |date=2013-11-14 |accessdate=2022-05-07 |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015549/https://www.poynter.org/reporting-editing/2013/politico-magazine-launches-online/ }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=About US |url=https://www.politico.com/magazine/about |website=Politico |accessdate=2022-05-07 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180902220709/https://www.politico.com/magazine/about |archivedate=2018-09-02}}</ref>。有别于专注“政治政策独家新闻”及突发报道的主站，杂志版提供“高影响力的杂志式报道”，比如长篇报道<ref name="Hare" /><ref name="Byersglasser">{{Cite web |last=Byers |first=Dylan |date=2013-06-02 |title=Politico hires FP's Susan Glasser to head new long-form journalism, opinion divisions |url=https://www.politico.com/blogs/media/2013/06/politico-hires-fps-susan-glasser-to-head-new-long-form-journalism-opinion-divisions-165226 |website=Politico |access-date=2020-06-30 |archive-date=2020-05-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200522205149/https://www.politico.com/blogs/media/2013/06/politico-hires-fps-susan-glasser-to-head-new-long-form-journalism-opinion-divisions-165226 }}</ref>。杂志第一任总编苏珊·格拉泽是《[[外交政策_(杂志)|外交政策]]》杂志的原编辑<ref name="Byersglasser" />，后两任是加雷特·格拉夫（Garrett Graff）和斯蒂芬·豪瑟（Stephen Heuser）。2016年12月，{{le|布莱克·洪谢尔|Blake Hounshell}}被任命为杂志新任主编<ref>{{Cite web |last=O'Shea |first=Chris |date=December 2016 |title=Blake Hounshell Named Editor of Politico Mag |url=https://www.adweek.com/digital/blake-hounshell-named-editor-of-politico-mag/ |website=AdWeek |access-date=2022-05-07 |archive-date=2020-12-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204171853/https://www.adweek.com/digital/blake-hounshell-named-editor-of-politico-mag/ }}</ref>。

除约3万名指定免费读者外，若要阅读杂志，每年须缴纳200美金的订阅费<ref>{{Cite news |last=Edmonds |first=Rick |date=2017-04-20 |title=Politico is trying to turn the business model for magazines on its head |language=en-US |work=Poynter Institute |url=http://www.poynter.org/2017/politico-is-trying-to-turn-the-business-model-for-magazines-on-its-head/456359/ |access-date=2017-07-28 |archive-date=2017-07-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170728080320/http://www.poynter.org/2017/politico-is-trying-to-turn-the-business-model-for-magazines-on-its-head/456359/ }}</ref>。杂志内容也可以在网上阅读<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hare |first=Kristen |date=2013-11-14 |title=Politico magazine launches online |url=https://www.poynter.org/2013/politico-magazine-launches-online/229767/ |access-date=2017-07-27 |website=Poynter Institute |archive-date=2017-08-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812052309/http://www.poynter.org/2013/politico-magazine-launches-online/229767/ }}</ref>。

=== 地方版 ===
2013年9月，政客收购在佛罗里达州和新泽西州各设有采访部门的《纽约首府报》（''Capital New York''）<ref>{{Cite web |last=Byers |first=Dylan |date=2013-09-08 |title=Politico buys Capital New York |url=https://www.politico.com/blogs/media/2013/09/politico-publisher-buys-capital-new-york-172096.html |website=Politico |access-date=2022-05-07 |archive-date=2015-06-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150628112036/http://www.politico.com/blogs/media/2013/09/politico-publisher-buys-capital-new-york-172096.html }}</ref>。2015年4月，政客宣布将原《纽约首府报》的报道版块更名为《政客佛罗里达》（''Politico Florida''）、《政客新泽西》（''Politico New Jersey''）和《政客纽约》（''Politico New York''），以扩大地方政治新闻的报道范围<ref>{{Cite news |last=Somaiya |first=Ravi |date=2015-04-15 |title=Politico to Expand Coverage of States, Starting With New Jersey |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/16/business/media/politico-to-expand-coverage-of-states-starting-with-new-jersey.html |access-date=2017-07-28 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2021-02-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210228035646/https://www.nytimes.com/2015/04/16/business/media/politico-to-expand-coverage-of-states-starting-with-new-jersey.html }}</ref>。2018年9月，政客宣布上线《政客加利福尼亚专业版》（''Politico California Pro''）<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pudwill |first=Katie |date=2018-09-26 |title=Politico Announces Expanded California Presence |language=en |work=Politico |url=https://www.politico.com/blogs/politico-press/2018/09/26/politico-announces-expanded-california-presence-843150 |access-date=2018-10-30 |archive-date=2020-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201130145946/https://www.politico.com/blogs/politico-press/2018/09/26/politico-announces-expanded-california-presence-843150 }}</ref>。

===海外扩张===
2014年9月，政客与德国出版商[[阿克塞爾·斯普林格集團|阿克塞爾·斯普林格集團]]成立合资企业，推出欧洲版，总部设在[[布鲁塞尔-首都大区|布鲁塞尔]]<ref>{{Cite news |last=Pallota, Frank |date=2014-09-09 |title=Politico's next battleground: Europe |work=CNN |url=https://money.cnn.com/2014/09/09/media/politico-europe-expansion/ |accessdate=2022-05-07 |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327051230/https://money.cnn.com/2014/09/09/media/politico-europe-expansion/ }}</ref>。2014年12月，新公司宣布收购法国头部新闻内容供应商国际发展研究所（Development Institute International），将欧洲政治报纸《{{tsl|en|Politico Europe|政客欧洲版|欧洲之声}}》更名为《{{tsl|en|Politico Europe|政客欧洲版}}》。首期报纸于2015年4月23日付梓<ref>{{Cite web |last=Jackson |first=Jasper |date=2015-03-17 |title=Politico to launch in Europe in April with more than 40 journalists |url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/mar/17/poltico-europe-axel-springer-brussels-paris-london-berlin |access-date=2021-02-12 |website=The Guardian |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108110029/https://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/mar/17/poltico-europe-axel-springer-brussels-paris-london-berlin }}</ref>。

2015年，报纸的网站{{tsl|en|Politico.eu|Politico.eu}}正式上线，到2016年初大约有50名编辑及20多名业务员。根据第三方机构的调查，在249个调查对象中，Politico.eu是布鲁塞尔阅读人数最多的媒体，影响仅次于《[[金融時報_(英國)|金融时报]]》、[[BBC新闻|BBC新闻]]及《[[经济学人|经济学人]]》<ref>{{cite web |last=Uberti |first=David |url=https://www.cjr.org/analysis/politico.php |title=What a major leadership change means for Politico’s global ambitions |date=2016-02-01 |accessdate=2022-05-07 |website=Columbia Journalism Review |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015537/https://www.cjr.org/analysis/politico.php |archivedate=2022-03-27}}</ref>。2021年3月18日，于2019年9月履新的《政客欧洲版》总编斯蒂芬·布朗（Stephen Brown）因心脏病猝逝，得年57岁<ref>{{Cite web |date=2019-09-29 |title=Press Release: Politico Europe names Stephen Brown Editor in Chief |url=https://www.politico.eu/politico-europe-names-stephen-brown-editor-in-chief/ |access-date=2019-11-11 |website=POLITICO |language=en-US |archive-date=2022-03-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220327015537/https://www.politico.eu/politico-europe-names-stephen-brown-editor-in-chief/ }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-03-19 |title=Stephen Brown, editor in chief of POLITICO Europe, is dead at 57 |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/stephen-brown-politico-obituary/ |access-date=2022-04-11 |website=POLITICO |language=en-US |archive-date=2022-04-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220407235433/https://www.politico.eu/article/stephen-brown-politico-obituary/ }}</ref>。

=== 调查报道 ===
在格拉泽及后任{{tsl|en|Carrie Budoff Brown|嘉莉·布道夫·布朗}}的率领下，政客深入调查华盛顿国会的丑闻内幕，导致多人引咎辞职。2015年，谢尔曼和帕梅尔发表一系列揭露伊利诺伊州众议员[[阿隆·夏克|阿隆·夏克]]丑闻的报道，导致后者引咎辞职<ref>{{Cite news |last=Rutenberg |first=Jim |date=2016-06-20 |title=Mike Allen, Politico’s Newsletter Pioneer, Is Handing Over the Reins |language=en-US |work=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/20/business/media/mike-allen-politicos-newsletter-pioneer-is-handing-over-the-reins.html |access-date=2022-04-11 |issn=0362-4331 |archive-date=2020-11-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108125728/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/20/business/media/mike-allen-politicos-newsletter-pioneer-is-handing-over-the-reins.html }}</ref>。2017年，记者玛丽安·莱文（Marianne Levine）揭露获特朗普提名劳工部长的[[安德鲁·普斯德|安德鲁·普斯德]]有虐待前妻的情况<ref>{{Cite web |date=2017-02-16 |title=How a Politico reporter helped bring down Trump's Labor Secretary pick |url=https://www.poynter.org/reporting-editing/2017/how-a-politico-reporter-helped-bring-down-trumps-labor-secretary-pick/ |access-date=2022-04-11 |website=Poynter |language=en-US |archive-date=2021-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210305080704/https://www.poynter.org/reporting-editing/2017/how-a-politico-reporter-helped-bring-down-trumps-labor-secretary-pick/ }}</ref>，导致他主动提出取消提名。

2017年9月，记者拉查娜·普拉丹（Rachana Pradhan）和丹·戴蒙德（Dan Diamond）披露特朗普政府卫生部长[[湯姆·普萊斯|湯姆·普萊斯]]用纳税人的钱坐私人飞机的丑闻<ref>{{Cite news |last=Wemple |first=Erik |date=2017-10-04 |title=Opinion: Stakeout at Dulles Airport launched Politico bombshell on Tom Price’s charter-flight scandal |work=The Washington Post |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/erik-wemple/wp/2017/10/04/stakeout-at-dulles-airport-launched-politico-bombshell-on-tom-prices-charter-flight-scandal/ |access-date=2022-04-11 |archive-date=2019-06-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190616114153/https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/erik-wemple/wp/2017/10/04/stakeout-at-dulles-airport-launched-politico-bombshell-on-tom-prices-charter-flight-scandal/ }}</ref>，导致普莱斯引咎辞职。

